analysis.transcript_summary: Lee discussed a matter for Chambers/Legal 500 submission. The matter involved advising Coca-Cola on a strategic acquisition of a soft drinks company in Indonesia for $287M USD. The team, led by Lee in London, advised on the end-to-end transaction, including tax, employment, and IP. Other team members were Sam Stump (San Diego, Employment), Andy Batty (San Francisco, Tax), and Edu Aguilar-Pélez (Detroit, IP). Garuda Indonesia served as Indonesian counsel. The deal closed on August 14th, 2025, and had press coverage.
